3. Replace the tablespoon of milk with a tablespoon of white vinegar. White vinegar is a common household acid that can be used to create a buttermilk substitute. The acidity in the vinegar will react with the baking soda in the pancake batter, producing a similar tangy flavor to buttermilk.
4. Let the mixture sit for twenty minutes. This allows the acid in the vinegar to fully react with the baking soda, creating a similar acidity to buttermilk. The longer it sits, the better the reaction will be.

