   - This method involves using a knife to cut the worm in half, which is a practical and effective way to prepare the worm for fishing. 
   - After cutting the worm in half, the fishing hook can be used to pierce one half of the worm, which is a common and effective way to attach the worm to the fishing line.

Based on the practicality and effectiveness of the methods, Solution 1 is the better option.

